"Northern Spy Food Co. served lunch to everyone who lined up outside their restaurant at Avenue A and 12th street - polenta, pork buns, chicken, biscuits and freshly baked cookies. They get props in my book; all this food was served to locals at no charge."... Read this in a gothamist article by Christopher Robbins, gotta say I have all the respect in the world for a company that has lost money all week due to the storm but still goes the extra mile to look out for their neighbors in a serious time of need..
